<section class="hero"><div class="container">
<div class="label">Fourth Circuit · West Virginia</div>
<h1>United States Bankruptcy Court for the Northern District of West Virginia</h1>
<p class="subtitle">United States Bankruptcy Court for the Northern District of West Virginia has processed 50,507 federal bankruptcy filings in the Federal Judicial Center Integrated Database, ranking 84th of 94 US bankruptcy districts by total case volume, with Chapter 7 accounting for 65.06% of classified filings.</p>
<div class="datastamp">Data updated <time datetime="2026-04-21">2026-04-21</time>. <a href="/research/methodology/">Methodology &amp; sources</a>.</div>
</div></section>
<main class="container">
<div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span><a href="/cases/">Cases</a><span class="sep">/</span>N.D.W. Va.</div>
<div class="stat-grid"><div class="stat-cell"><span class="v">50,507</span><span class="k">Total cases (FJC IDB)</span></div><div class="stat-cell"><span class="v">1,135</span><span class="k">FY 2025 filings</span></div><div class="stat-cell"><span class="v">33.73%</span><span class="k">Chapter 13 share</span></div><div class="stat-cell"><span class="v">65.06%</span><span class="k">Chapter 7 share</span></div><div class="stat-cell"><span class="v">19.96%</span><span class="k">Prior-filer rate (Ch 13)</span></div><div class="stat-cell"><span class="v">0.0%</span><span class="k">RECAP coverage</span></div></div><p class="datastamp">National rank: <strong>84th of 94</strong> by total case volume (12th percentile). See all rankings below.</p>
<section id="filings">
<h2><span class="label">Section 01</span>Filing Volume</h2>
<p>Annual federal bankruptcy filings in N.D.W. Va., FY 2010–2026. The most recent fiscal year is rendered with a muted marker to indicate its incomplete status.</p>
